               <item n="project_comment_old">&lt;p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;line a1: translation above as in [[Carling, DThTA]]: 58; on p.36, the translation runs "this world, wrapped in ignorance, is complete darkness" (TI)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translation in [[Meunier 2013]] (125, 132): &lt;b&gt;a4&lt;/b&gt; "Pour les deux, tu es celui qui révèle le moyen aux dieux et aux humains." –Martin (Mon, 2014-08-25, 12:41:44)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Transcription in [[Meunier 2013]] (131-132): &lt;b&gt;a4&lt;/b&gt; &lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="color: red;"&gt;āmpine upāy&lt;/span&gt; ñäktas napeṃśśi ...&lt;/i&gt;. –Martin (Thu, 2015-04-30, 18:45:27)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translation in [[Adams 2012a]] (28): &lt;b&gt;a1-2&lt;/b&gt; "however, by thy body [is] the whole of the Three Worlds illuminated by knowledge". –Martin (Mon, 2015-08-17, 22:35:03 (CEST))&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</item>
